Analysis.name: Ulcer complications
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: The randomization process is well-detailed; however, in Table 1, some categories appear unbalanced. For example: Other Types of Arthritis: Esomeprazole 19 (14%) Placebo 12 (9%)
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: The authors report that the study was a double-blind, placebo-matching study, and its analysis was appropriate as the authors performed an intention-to-treat analysis.
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: An intention-to-treat analysis was conducted on all randomized patients, and data are available for all randomized participants
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: The methodology for assessing the outcome variable was appropriate and was performed consistently in both groups.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: The analysis was prespecified in the study protocol, and intention-to-treat analysis was performed. Lost data was also declared.
Overall.bias.support: The study is judged to be at low risk of bias for this result

Analysis.name: Ulcer complications
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: The only information about randomisation is the statement that the study is randomised. There were imbalances between study groups.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: The study follows a double-blind approach. A small number of participants were excluded post-randomisation but it was judged to not affect the results.
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Information for this outcome was available for all study participants.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: The outcome measure was the same in both groups.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: Study protocol not available. The study methods section reports assessing outcomes at 1 and 3 months but the results section only reports at 3 months. The statistical analysis section provides insight into how the data for this outcome was treated and conducted.
Overall.bias.support: The study is judged to be at high risk of bias for this result.

Analysis.name: Adverse events
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: It was a randomized double-blind, placebo-controlled, parallel-group study comparing omeprazole 20 mg o.m. with a placebo, given for up to 6 months. Table 1.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: It was a randomised double-blind, placebo-controlled, parallel-group study comparing omeprazole 20 mg o.m. with placebo, given for up to 6 months. The study followed a double-blind approach, Inappropiat analyses were used for estimating the effects of the assessment on the intervention.
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Data available for nearly all participants were randomised.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: The method for outcome assessment was probably the same for both groups and consistent across groups.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: No pre-specified analysis plan or protocol is available. No information about outcome measurement definitions. There were no multiple analyses for this outcome.
Overall.bias.support: The study is judged to raise some concerns for this result because of issues related to the selection of the reported result.
